cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with a problem in hyperspectral imaging, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel regularization approach, which involves optimization techniques (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.IT). The method also involves spatial decomposition and superpixels, which are commonly used in image processing and segmentation (cs.SI, cs.MM).
